      "patchset_number": 4,
      "line": 201,
      "message": "This shall be \"---\" only.\n\"...\" shows the end of the file, not the end of a YAML document. See YAML spec: https://yaml.org/spec/1.0/\n\nCitation: \"YAML uses three dashes (“---”) to separate documents within a stream. Comment lines begin with the pound sign (“#”). Three dots (“...”) indicate the end of a document without starting a new one, for use in communication channels.\"\n\nSo \"...\" are applicable after the last YAML document only.\nA different approach taken here might have influence on certain YAML parsers.",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 5597,
        "name": "Damian Nowak",
        "display_name": "Damian Nowak",
        "email": "damian.nowak@nokia.com",
        "username": "deen1985"
      },
      "updated": "2020-02-24 11:00:11.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": null,
      "unresolved": false
    },
    {
      "id": "b6aec570_90111c15",
      "file_path": "docs/Chapter8/VES_Registraion_3_2.rst",
      "patchset_number": 4,
      "line": 205,
      "message": "As before: \"---\" is appilcable here, not \"--- ...\"",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 5597,
